This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) and their implementation for on-device low-power online learning and inference. Additionally, the paper proposes a Federated Learning (FL) approach for cooperative training of networked on-device SNNs. 

The paper also touches upon topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of SNNs for edge intelligence, which involves processing data at the edge of a network rather than sending it to a central location, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of SNNs for computer vision tasks, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
